<TITLE> Two more special aides to CA </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 21 (bdnews24.com)  Two more persons have been appointed to chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed as special assistants, the government said in a circular Monday. One of the two special aides is Singer Bangladesh's chairman and managing director Mahbub Jamil. Jamil is the first special assistant to the CA to be appointed with status of a minister. He has been tasked with civil aviation and tourism, industries and youth and sports portfolios, the chief adviser's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim told bdnews24.com. The second aide is Manik Lal Samaddar, former secretary of the Implementation Monitoring and Evaluation Division. Samaddarappointed with status of a state ministerhas been assigned to the fisheries and livestock and science and information and communication technology ministries. bdnews2
